Task: Add custom events in components

 <p>Dioxus components can add <a href="https://dioxuslabs.com/learn/0.7/essentials/basics/event_handlers" rel="nofollow noreferrer">EventHandlers</a> on predefined Node attributes<br />
eg:</p>
<pre><code>fn app() -&gt; Element {
    let mut moveCount = use_signal(|| 0);

    rsx! {
        h1 { &quot;Mouse mouvement counter: {count}&quot; }
        div { onmousemove: move |_| count += 1 }
    }
}
</code></pre>
<p>I'd like to find a way to add EventHandlers to respond to custom events, without having to change my state and rebuild the whole component tree.</p>
<p>More specifically, I'm trying to make draggable SVG elements.<br />
Because SVG does not have drag events ('onDrag', 'onDragStop', etc), I'd like to have a wrapper component to handle the mouse position and dragged element, and 'pass' the mouse position to the dragged children so it can change it's position on the screen.</p>
<p>Naïve implementation (breaks when the mouse leaves the dragged element) :</p>
<pre><code>#[component]
